course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 35m
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}(peeled and diced). Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{6%ounce}(trimmed and cut into ¼-inch-thick rounds). Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}(minced). Remove and discard any large stems from @Kale{4%ounce}(stems removed).

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large #pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and carrots; season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Italian Seasoning{1%tablespoon} and garlic into pot with veggies. Cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @Crushed Tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @Veggie Stock Concentrate{3}, 3 cups water (6 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until carrots are just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once carrots are just softened, stir in @Israeli Couscous{2.5%ounce} and kale. Cook until couscous is tender and kale is wilted, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

== Garlic Bread ==

While soup cooks, halve @Demi-Baguette{1} lengthwise.

Place @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} (all for 4) and season with salt and pepper.

Toast baguette halves, then spread cut sides with garlic butter. Halve each piece on a diagonal.

== To Serve ==

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Parmesan Cheese{3%tablespoon} and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with garlic bread on the side.

> No matter the weather, it’s tough not to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the culinary equivalent of a bear hug). This hearty, soul-warming veggie rendition is chock-full of goodness—that’s to say carrots, onion, crushed tomatoes, a bevy of Italian herbs and spices, chewy couscous, and tender kale. And because no good brothy bowl is complete without something delicious for dunking, we're also throwing in a side of toasty, buttery garlic bread. Soup's on!